            "question_text": "Given \\(h(x) = 3g(x)\\), state the coordinates of the minimum point of the function \\(h(x)\\).",
            "solution_text": "The minimum point of \\(g(x)\\) is at \\((2, -1)\\).  When we multiply a function by a constant, the x-coordinate of the minimum point remains unchanged.  The y-coordinate is multiplied by the constant. Therefore, the minimum point of \\(h(x) = 3g(x)\\) is at \\((2, 3 \\times -1)\\), which simplifies to \\((2, -3)\\)."
